# SmartPerfetto root env example (Docker)
# Do not edit .env.example directly. Copy it to .env for Docker Hub or source
# Docker Compose:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Local source users usually want backend/.env instead:
#   cp backend/.env.example backend/.env
#
# If local `claude` already works in the same terminal, no AI env is needed for
# source runs. Docker cannot see host Claude Code auth, so Docker needs either
# the UI Provider Manager or one explicit provider block below. Keep unused
# credential lines commented.
#
# Short answer: Claude Code, OpenAI Agents SDK, Pi Agent Core, and OpenCode are
# alternatives. You do not configure multiple runtimes for first setup. Pick the
# UI Provider Manager, one Claude-compatible block, one OpenAI-compatible block,
# the Pi Agent Core block, or the OpenCode block.
#
# Beginner rule:
#   1. Uncomment exactly ONE provider block below. If a provider shows both
#      Claude-compatible and OpenAI-compatible alternatives, choose one side.
#   2. Replace only placeholders like your_*_api_key_here, sk-your-*, model IDs,
#      or Base URLs when your provider console says they differ.
#   3. Restart the backend/container after editing this file.
#   4. If a UI Provider Manager profile is active, it overrides this .env file.
#      Choose System Default in the provider switcher to use this file again.

# ---------------------------------------------------
# Server
# ---------------------------------------------------
# SMARTPERFETTO_BACKEND_PORT is the preferred backend port setting.
# PORT is kept for Node/Docker/PaaS compatibility and is used as a fallback.
SMARTPERFETTO_BACKEND_PORT=3000
SMARTPERFETTO_FRONTEND_PORT=10000
# Native source runs listen on loopback by default. Docker overrides the
# container-side bind host while publishing ports on 127.0.0.1 by default.
# SMARTPERFETTO_BIND_HOST=127.0.0.1
# SMARTPERFETTO_PUBLISH_HOST=127.0.0.1
# Set this for reverse proxies, HTTPS deployments, or Docker host ports that
# differ from the container's backend listen port.
# SMARTPERFETTO_BACKEND_PUBLIC_URL=http://localhost:3000
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=development
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:10000

# Backend API Authentication (recommended in any shared environment)
# This protects SmartPerfetto backend APIs. It is not a model provider API key;
# model provider keys belong in exactly one provider block below or in the UI
# Provider Manager. Leave unset for local single-user runs. When set, this is
# the deployment operator credential and has local administration authority;
# issue scoped enterprise API keys to ordinary users instead of sharing it.
# SMARTPERFETTO_API_KEY=replace_with_a_strong_random_secret
# Enterprise mode disables unauthenticated dev fallback. SSO trusted headers are
# only safe behind an OIDC-authenticated reverse proxy that strips inbound
# client-supplied SSO headers.
# SMARTPERFETTO_ENTERPRISE=false
# Enterprise storage starts in dual-write/filesystem-authoritative mode so
# existing local registries remain visible. DB cutover is an explicit,
# snapshot-backed operation after reconciliation.
# SMARTPERFETTO_ENTERPRISE_MIGRATION_PHASE=dual-write
# SMARTPERFETTO_ENTERPRISE_CUTOVER_CONFIRMED=false
# SMARTPERFETTO_SSO_TRUSTED_HEADERS=false
# SMARTPERFETTO_SSO_COOKIE_SECRET=replace_with_a_32_byte_random_secret
# Enterprise provider endpoints default to public HTTPS. Audited private
# gateways require exact origins (scheme + host + port), comma-separated.
# Wildcards and URL paths are not accepted.
# SMARTPERFETTO_PROVIDER_PRIVATE_ENDPOINT_ALLOWLIST=https://llm.internal.example:8443
# Dedicated 32+ byte secret for short-lived browser WebSocket capabilities to
# the trace-processor proxy. Set it explicitly for enterprise/shared deployments;
# rotating it invalidates outstanding capabilities without exposing the API key.
# SMARTPERFETTO_TP_PROXY_CAPABILITY_SECRET=replace_with_a_32_byte_random_secret
# SMARTPERFETTO_OIDC_ISSUER_URL=https://idp.example.com
# SMARTPERFETTO_OIDC_CLIENT_ID=smartperfetto
# SMARTPERFETTO_OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=replace_with_oidc_client_secret
# SMARTPERFETTO_OIDC_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/auth/oidc/callback
# SMARTPERFETTO_OIDC_EMAIL_DOMAIN_MAP=example.com=default-dev-tenant

# Optional private Android knowledge roots (Docker paths, separated by the
# platform path delimiter). The default is empty/deny. Mount the repository
# read-only into the container and list only its canonical root here.
# SMARTPERFETTO_KNOWLEDGE_ROOTS=/knowledge/android-internals-wiki

# ---------------------------------------------------
# AI runtime
# ---------------------------------------------------
# Default runtime is claude-agent-sdk when no provider/env override is set.
# Valid values: claude-agent-sdk, openai-agents-sdk, pi-agent-core, opencode.
# These are alternative runtime paths, not two setup steps to complete.
# For first setup, do not enable both ANTHROPIC_* and OPENAI_*. In advanced
# deployments where both are present, SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME selects the
# active side. Without it, SmartPerfetto still defaults to Claude.

# Option 1: Anthropic direct
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here
# CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# CLAUDE_LIGHT_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5

# Option 2: OpenAI direct
# SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME=openai-agents-sdk
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# OPENAI_AGENTS_PROTOCOL=responses
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.5
# OPENAI_LIGHT_MODEL=gpt-5.4-mini

# Option 2b: Pi Agent Core
# Pi Agent Core is optional. With a real model config it uses SmartPerfetto's
# shared prompt, SQL/Skill, plan/hypothesis, and report pipeline. It is
# dynamically loaded from @earendil-works/pi-agent-core and does not enable .pi
# project discovery, package extensions, shell tools, or file tools.
# Prefer Provider Manager custom providers for this runtime. For env fallback:
# SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME=pi-agent-core
# SMARTPERFETTO_PI_AGENT_CORE_MODEL_JSON={"id":"your-model-id","name":"Your Model","api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","baseUrl":"https://api.openai.com/v1","reasoning":false,"input":["text"],"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0},"contextWindow":128000,"maxTokens":4096,"apiKeyEnv":"OPENAI_API_KEY"}
# Use "api":"openai-completions" for OpenAI-compatible chat/completions
# gateways; the example above targets official OpenAI Responses.
# Optional: use a local package checkout or unpacked npm package.
# SMARTPERFETTO_PI_AGENT_CORE_MODULE_PATH=/absolute/path/to/@earendil-works/pi-agent-core/dist/index.js
# Optional runtime-level prompt; SmartPerfetto analysis contracts still come
# from backend strategies.
# SMARTPERFETTO_PI_AGENT_CORE_SYSTEM_PROMPT=

# Option 2c: OpenCode
# OpenCode is optional. It runs a hardened isolated OpenCode server, uses
# explicit Provider Manager/env model configuration, and exposes only
# request-scoped SmartPerfetto MCP tools. It does not read your personal
# OpenCode login, project config, extensions, shell tools, or file tools.
# Prefer Provider Manager custom providers for this runtime. For env fallback:
# SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME=opencode
# Recommended when you want OpenCode-specific model/provider wiring:
# SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_MODEL_JSON={"providerID":"smartperfetto","modelID":"your-model-id","baseUrl":"https://api.openai.com/v1","apiKeyEnv":"OPENAI_API_KEY","smallModel":"your-light-model"}
# Or omit SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_MODEL_JSON and use OPENAI_BASE_URL,
# OPENAI_API_KEY, OPENAI_MODEL, and OPENAI_LIGHT_MODEL below.
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_provider_api_key_here
# OPENAI_MODEL=your-model-id
# OPENAI_LIGHT_MODEL=your-light-model
# Optional: use a local package checkout or unpacked npm package.
# SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_SDK_MODULE_PATH=/absolute/path/to/@opencode-ai/sdk/dist/index.js
# Optional: isolated project directory; otherwise SmartPerfetto creates a temp directory.
# SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_PROJECT_DIR=/absolute/path/to/empty/project
# Optional runtime-level prompt; SmartPerfetto analysis contracts still come
# from backend strategies.
# SMARTPERFETTO_OPENCODE_SYSTEM_PROMPT=

# Option 3: Third-party provider presets
# Uncomment ONE runtime side for ONE provider. Treat prefilled Base URLs as
# starting points; usually you only replace the key, but provider-console URLs
# take precedence.
# SmartPerfetto uses CLAUDE_MODEL / CLAUDE_LIGHT_MODEL, not ANTHROPIC_MODEL.
# Prefilled Base URLs below are based on public provider information and may be
# incomplete, stale, account-specific, or region-specific. If analysis fails at
# connection/tool-call time, verify both the Base URL and model IDs in your
# provider console first. Please open an issue or PR when a public preset needs
# to be corrected.

# DeepSeek
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=your_deepseek_api_key_here
# CLAUDE_MODEL=deepseek-v4-pro
# CLAUDE_LIGHT_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash
#
# DeepSeek OpenAI-compatible alternative:
# SMARTPERFETTO_AGENT_RUNTIME=openai-agents-sdk
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/v1
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_deepseek_api_key_here
# OPENAI_AGENTS_PROTOCOL=chat_completions
# OPENAI_MODEL=deepseek-v4-pro
# OPENAI_LIGHT_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash

